Mozambique May Achieve 8%, 10% Growth on Management, Columbia’s Sachs Says

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-06-23T06:08:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/mozambique-may-achieve-8-10-growth-on-management-columbia-s-sachs-says.html
Mozambique’s economy could expand by
between 8 percent and 10 percent if the nation’s resources are
properly managed, Columbia University professor Jeffrey Sachs
said.  The southern African nation’s mining industry is part of
the equation for growth, Sachs, who is advising the Mozambican
government, said in an interview today in the capital, Maputo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
